node.text:
Thank you for sharing in our joy 💗. This video explains step by step how to create the green screen effect to make it look like the baby ultrasound is appearing over the skin as well as the gender reveal portion. 
The two video editing apps I used are Splice and Videoleap. You can use the same soundtrack by going to the original Reel video of the pregnancy announcement and clicking on the audio ❤️.

node.title: Pregnancy Announcement- How to create green screen effect

node.text: Come inside my car, well my husbands car (long story 😆), and watch Michelle from @safeintheseat share information on transitioning from one car seat to another, forward facing vs. front facing, booster seats vs harness car seats, and so much more. We even touched on the subject of carpool and fitting as many car seats as possible in the car. Really valuable safety information, thank you @safeintheseat 🚙❤️. Every week in October we will be sharing a safe activity to do in the car so keep a close eye out for that 🤗 #motherhood #momlife #safetyfirst #carseat #preschool #parenting #carsafety

Anyone else obsessed? 🙋🏻‍♀️ These are my top three favorite techniques. If I had to choose one, I would go with he ice technique. It gives it the coolest kaleidoscope look. Let me know which one is your favorite ❤️
•
🧊ICE TECHNIQUE🧊
1️⃣Soak your fabric in water and strain out any excess water. 
2️⃣Lay your shirt flat and use a fork to help create a swirl. Make two or three different swirls on the shirt. All in opposite directions. 
3️⃣Secure it using rubber bands
4️⃣Place the shirt on a rack with a bin underneath to catch any falling dye.
5️⃣Add a circular rim around the shirt to help hold ice in place. You can staple a piece of paper together to fit perfectly around the tied up shirt.
6️⃣Add ice on top of the shirt
7️⃣Sprinkle the dye powder onto of the ice. Note that it’s the dye powder, not the dye solution. Use one set of colors on one side of the shirt and another set on the other side.
8️⃣Wait for the ice to melt and turn the shirt over. Repeat steps 6 & 7.
9️⃣Place the shirt in a bag and wait at least 6 hours
🔟Remove the shirt from the bag and cut the rubber bands off.
1️⃣1️⃣Run the shirt under water until the water runs clear
1️⃣2️⃣Put the shirt to wash all on its own using cold water. Dry it and its all done 😃
•
❤️HEART DESIGN ❤️(minute 1:43)
1️⃣Soak your fabric in water and strain out any excess water. 
2️⃣Lay your shirt flat and fold in half. 
3️⃣Place a heart cut out on top and trace half of it onto the shirt using a washable marker. Very important it’s washable.
4️⃣Slowly crinkle the shirt together following the heart line. Ultimately the line must be straight for the design to work.
5️⃣Secure the shirt together by adding a rubber band around the line. Add more rubber bands as you go down the shirt. One section per color you want to use.
6️⃣Mix your dye powder with water and squirt it onto the shirt. One color per section. Make sure to get both sides.
7️⃣Place the shirt in a bag and wait at least 6 hours
8️⃣Remove the shirt from the bag and cut the rubber bands off.
9️⃣Run the shirt under water until the water runs clear
🔟Put the shirt to wash all on its own using cold water. Dry it and its all done 😃

node.text:
Quarantine edition 😉. My best tip for fostering independent play is having a clear and inviting play area. Whether it is in the living room, bedroom or its own designated play space, the room should feel and look like you yourself want to play in it. This method of rotating toys and cleaning up the play space once a month or every couple of months has changed our life at home and saved us a ton of money 😎. At the end of the video, I show how and where I store toys that are out of rotation and art supplies❤️. •
Even though I speak with confidence, I have no idea what I’m doing here 😂. This is just what works for us 😉. Whats your toy/play space situation like?
•
👉🏼That being said, let’s talk about setting up the play space😜. ❤️Furniture is key. Choose storage shelves with simple, clean lines. It helps make the area look organized even if it is cluttered with toys. I love open shelves such as the cubbed ones from Target as well as the Trofast system from Ikea (the one with white drawers).
🧡Separate your toys into 4. Store 3/4 of the toys and keep out only 1/4. 💛Always keep out favorite toys. Keep them out but move them around the play space to keep it fresh. 💚If you have 50 toy cars, only leave out 10 in the drawer. Repeat this for any toys you have a lot of. Store the rest and take them out every time you rotate the toys. 💙Get rid of all the small toys that really play no part. You know, the ones we get from birthday parties 😬. Just toss or donate them. Those are one and done toys. 💜Hall out toys your kids have outgrown. This one is particularly difficult as we tend to get emotionally attached to items that trigger memories. Baby toys are really hard to get rid of but it is necessary for keeping an organized play space. 💖Showcase toys as if you were in a storefront. Its clean, inviting and draws you right in. •
❣️You can find all of the toys in here on my Amazon page (link in bio)

node.title: Ocean sensory bin- made with stuff from around the house 🌊

node.text:
Do you feel like toys are taking over your house? 😅 Just slowly being swallowed by toys that no one really plays with? I so felt that way a couple of years ago. Miss matched toys everywhere. A lot of little bits here and there from random birthday parties and lost pieces all over the place. My girls weren’t even really playing with anything which made it even more annoying. I got fed up one day and literally got rid of half of their toys. I organized the rest and here we are today😍. This was a process. A long one but it has been the absolute best thing for us. My girls actually started playing independently and there’s no longer toys everywhere. It made our lives at home much more enjoyable 🤗
•
👉🏼What I did:
❤️Organized their toys into categories (Example: literacy, numeracy, pretend play, DIY, fine motor skills, Dolls, Kitchen/cooking, building, art, books). 🧡I split each category into four. Stored 3/4 of the toys and put out the rest for the girls to play with. This started the toy rotation system. Keep in mind that I always keep out absolute favorites and just change them around. 💛I rotate the toys from storage to the play space every month or so. This gives old toys new life and in return, we hardly ever buy new toys. 💚Rotation day is my day to deep clean and reorganize. Getting rid of all the little birthday party gifts 😉
💙Toy display is important. I showcase them like in a store. Clearly visible and decluttered. For example, take out a toy set from the box and put it on a flat tray. It entices you to play with it and keep it organized on a tray. Don’t over stuff drawers. Add just a few cars, not the whole collection.
💜Made a self serve art area. Having simple things like paper and markers available to them at their level has been amazing for independent playtime. •
There is so much more I want to tell you. Make sure to check out my stories today. Let me know if you have any questions. Answering them all in the comments ❤️ #mothercould

🤸🏻‍♀️ INDOOR EXERCISE 🏠
At home Olympics anyone? 🥇 Save this for a rainy day! All you need is a roll of tape. It doesn’t have to be rainbow 😜. Also some jumbo letters if you have some randomly around the house 🙋🏻‍♀️😉. Recently, we did an outdoors track using chalk but chalk fades away while tape lasts a bit longer 😃. Use masking/painters tape to make it super easy to remove. 
•
👉🏼Here are the things I put on the track and some other ideas too:
-Hop scotch 
-Run line
-Frog jumps 
-Hot stones
-Jumping Jax
-Balance line (while singing the abc’s)
-Name letter hop on one foot 
-Jump in the box
-Zigzag jog line 
-Hop from one to the other
-crisscross jumps 
-Alphabet bubbles 
-Walk backwards
-Army crawl
-Lunges from one spot to the other 
•
🙏🏼Please suggest other ones in the comments ❤️ #mothercould
.
.
.

node.text: I love this paint recipe so much 🌈. Taste safe, easy to make, washable and SO vibrant 🤩. Just mix 2 parts water to 1 part corn starch and add a drop or two of food coloring. Mix well and take outdoors for some chalk painting 🎨. Kim @bestideasforkids shared a similar recipe last summer and I’ve been obsessed ever since 🙌🏻. Paint on anything and just hose down afterwards. Washes off really easily! It’s most vibrant on black pavement 🤩. #diy #summervibes #summeractivities #kidsactivities #sensoryplay #reels #preschool #motherhood #instagram #parenting #montessori #crafty #kidsart #momlife #toddlerlife #toddler

Lava lamps are so fun and simple to make using common household items. This time we made them cat-tastic! My kids love Gabby’s Dollhouse on Netflix so we themed these lamps to play alongside Gabby and her GabbyCat friends #AD. There are all new #GabbysDollhouse toys now available in-store & online like the fantastical dollhouse and magical musical cat ears shown in video! We CANNOT wait for new episodes of Gabby’s Dollhouse coming to Netflix August 10! My kids have watched every episode of season 1 a gazillion times 😸 @dreamworksjr 
·
To make the lava lamps 
👉🏼YOU’LL NEED:
-Water
-Oil
-Food coloring
-Effervescent tablets
👉🏼INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣Fill the container 1/3 of the way with water.
2️⃣Add a few drops of food coloring to the water. Swirl around to mix in.
3️⃣Fill the rest of the bottle with oil. Leave some space at the top for air bubbles.
4️⃣Decorate the bottle. I used a permanent marker to draw the face, pipe cleaners as whiskers and foam sheet cut outs for the ears. 
5️⃣Drop in the effervescent tablets and watch it bubble up.
💡Use sealable containers to repeat the experiment over and over without having to toss it.

🌋 TUBES OF EMOTION 🤪
An emotional twist on the classic baking soda and vinegar experiment 😉. Colors can represent emotions and is a wonderful way to get kids taking about feelings 🌈. Yellow 🌞 is typically a happy color and red can represent anger 😡. This fun visual helps associate colors with different emotions. But also, just because a color usually represents a certain emotion, it isn’t always the case. Blue, for example, can be sadness (like tears 😭) but it can also be calming (like the ocean 🌊). You can give your little ones droppers to practice fine motor skills too 👌.
💡Vinegar tip: Add a bit of water to it to make it last longer. I do 2/3 cup vinegar and 1/3 cup water.
•
👉🏼YOU’LL NEED:
-Paper rolls (I used towel paper rolls and cut them in thirds)
-Black marker
-2 tbsp baking soda per roll
-Food coloring
-Vinegar 
👉🏼INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣Draw faces on the front of the paper rolls
2️⃣Stand them up on a tray
3️⃣Carefully add 2 tbsp fo baking soda to each roll
4️⃣Add a drop of food coloring right on top of the baking soda (no need to mix)
5️⃣Pour vinegar inside the paper roll and watch it erupt. #mothercould 
.

node.text: After 1 month of camp, three lost water bottles and a few towels down, I made my daughter a reusable checklist of things in her backpack. Visual reminders always helps 🥳. Pictures and words to make it easy to identify plus a dry erase marker to check off the items. If you have a little one who often leaves things behind, give this a try ❤️. Added bonus- it helps me remember what to back in her bag every day 🤪. I used Canva (free app) to customize the template, printed and cut it out, then laminated it using self seal laminating sheets from Scotch brand. It was SO easy and will help a ton. Already making one for the school year 😂. We lost so many sweaters last year 🙃. Hope this helps you too 😘. #parenting #momhacks #momlife #toddlerlife #motherhood #preschool #schoolready #montessori #iteachtoo #teacher #homeschool #instagram

Toddler Myriam is back testing DIY less mess paint cups 😜. All you need is a balloon to make this happen! Perfect opportunity to reuse deflated balloons from birthday parties 😉. These help prevent spills and take off excess paint from the brushes to avoid splatter. They work so well!! To make them, 👉🏼YOU’LL NEED:
-Small hard plastic cups or small thick glass jars
-Balloons
-Scissors
-Paint
-Paint brushes
👉🏼INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣Cut the stem of the balloon off
2️⃣Add paint to the cup
3️⃣Stretch the balloon and add it to the opening of the cup. Make sure its nice and tight
4️⃣Cut a hole at the top of the balloon. Don’t cut it off though, just make an opening for the paint brush
5️⃣Insert the paint brush through the hole and you’re all done. #recycleandplay #diy #crafty #lifehack #kidsart #momhacks #momlife #toddlerlife #motherhood #parenting #instagram #toddler #kidsactivities #preschool #reuse #reels #montessori

🦈JELLO RESCUE🐬
Shark week called for a rescue activity, a squishy one that is 😜. Help the sharks out of “thick water”. This makes my kids feel like superheroes + it’s taste safe 🥳. It can be adjusted for babies, just add more water so the gelatin is softer and add bigger toys (if it fits inside a paper roll, it’s too small 👀). 
One thing to consider ➡️. Use plain gelatin! You can certainly make this activity with regular jello but it will be suuuuper sticky due to the sugar😅. By using plain gelatin, you avoid the stickiness and it taste gross. Your little ones will most likely spit it out as soon as they try it😝.
•
👉🏼YOU’LL NEED:
-Gelatin 
-Animals or anything you want your kids to find
👉🏼INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣Make clear gelatin following the instructions on the box. Use only 3/4 of the recommended water to make the gelatin. This will  make it more stiff and harder to rescue the items.
2️⃣Insert the toys in the gelatin. 
3️⃣Place in the refrigerator until it fully sets.
4️⃣Remove from the refrigerator and have your child rescue the items.
⚠️Gelatin/jello is a choking hazard. Make sure to supervise your children at all times during this activity. #mothercould #sharkweek 
.

Grow your own crystals at home!! ✨ Whoa! I don’t know who was more impressed, me or the kids 🤪. I shaped some pipe cleaners to form their names and grew crystals around the letters. These are for sure going up as decoration in their rooms. SO cool! 🤩. 
👉🏼YOU’LL NEED: -4 tbsp Borax for ever 1 cup of water -Pipe cleaner
-Craft stick
-String
-Long jar/vase
👉🏼INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣Shape the pipe cleaners into the desired shape of your finished crystals. For the name, use small pieces of pipe cleaner to tie the letters together tightly.
2️⃣Measure out how much water you will need to cover your shape. Boil the water and pour into the jar.
3️⃣Add about 3-4 Tbsp of Borax for every cup of water and mix until fully dissolved.
4️⃣Use the string to tie your pipe cleaners to the craft stick and leave the craft stick over the rim of each jar so that the pipe cleaners are suspended in the water.
5️⃣Leave it in the solution for 24 hrs.
6️⃣After 24hrs, remove from the solution and allow it to dry for 24hrs.
⚠️Borax should never be left to handle alone by children. Adult supervision required. 
In my opinion, the crystals look a bit like rock candy therefore I do not leave the finished product alone with my kids. Too much temptation 😆. #diy #science #scienceforkids #recycleandplay #kidsactivities #momlife #toddler #motherhood #parenting #preschool #montessori #instagram #crafty #reels

3 ways to make writing practice fun 💃🏻. 
Messy ➡️ Shaving cream tray
Less messy ➡️ Salt tray
No mess ➡️ Gel sensory bag
Which ones your favorite? Guess mine 😜. 
❣️Practice writing letters, numbers, shapes or even just make lines!
•
To color salt, 👉🏼YOU ‘LL NEED:
-Table salt
-Food coloring
-Zip close bag or container
👉🏼INSTRUCTIONS: 
1️⃣Pour a bit of salt into a zip close bag. 
2️⃣Add a few drops of food coloring to the bag. The more you add, the deeper the color will be. 
4️⃣Remove all the air from the bag and close it well. 
5️⃣Shake until all of the salt is evenly coated. 
6️⃣Pour out the salt onto a tray and let it dry a few minutes. 
•
To make the gel bag, 👉🏼YOU’LL NEED:
-Gallon size freezer ziplock bag
-Hair gel (mine is from the dollar store)
-Food coloring and glitter optional
👉🏼INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣Add a bit of hair gel to the bag. 
2️⃣Add a couple drops of food coloring and mix.
3️⃣Seal the bag leaving little to no air inside. 
5️⃣Have your child mix the colors inside the bag. #learningthroughplay #kidsactivities #recycleandplay #preaschool #instagram #montessori #diy #reels #toddler #sensoryplay #motherhood

node.text: Sand toys not just for the beach 😎. Such a fun way to cool down on a really hot day ☀️. We saw this idea last year from @curious_columbus and have been making all sorts of ice castles ever since 🏰. Simply fill sand castle molds with water and some toys to rescue. Freeze it overnight and it’s ready! Offer some fine motor tools like droppers to squeeze warm water on the castle. My kids love to carve out sea animals 😍. Hope you give it a try 😘 #summeractivities #kidsactivities #instagram #motherhood #reels #parenting #montessori #recycleandplay #mothercould #preschool #toddler #toddlerlife #momlife
